snippet.textDisplay:
Ruiz was seriously frustrated in this fight. It wasn't just with Joshua's movement, but his punches that felled Joshua the last time were not having the desired effect. See 43:27 and 43:31 .... especially the latter hit from Ruiz, it was exactly the same punch that sent Joshua to the canvas the last time, in fact, this was a combo. Joshua took them and tried to tie him, but Ruiz added another combo about 12 seconds before the end of that round, yet Joshua shook them off. That was frustrating.
..... The snappy jabs also wore him down. Joshua hit him with some big shots that would have kissed Wilder or Fury goodnight!
..... Credit to Andy Ruiz, a fighter, but Joshua was the better boxer on the night. Joshua proved that he can mix it.

snippet.textDisplay: Many fans have called this fight "boring" but I wonder if the "boring" tag is almost an "after the event" reaction. ( or even watching the fight the following day, when knowing the result ). For example, all the way through the fight, I was on the edge of my seat expecting Andy to launch a vicious sustained attack on Joshua at any second,  And, on the other hand, wondering if Joshua - from somewhere, would suddenly  produce one of his fight ending big blows, But, when the fight had ended, maybe that's when thoughts of  a "boring fight" entered the fans' heads.
